<p class="headerpath" style="text-align: center;"><span class="UI_COMMAND_NOBOLD" id="MenuBar_Document_Modify.msg+MenuBar_Document_Modify+6835">Modify</span><img src="../../../images/general/litarr.gif"> <span class="UI_COMMAND_NOBOLD" id="MenuBar_Document_Modify_Curve.msg+MenuBar_Document_Modify_Curve+1109">Curve</span><img src="../../../images/general/litarr.gif"> <span class="UI_COMMAND_NOBOLD" id="MenuBar_Document_Modify_Curve.msg+MenuBar_Document_Modify_Curve+1123">Split</span> </p>
<hr color="#63a9d8">
</table>

<br>
</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0;">The <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+123">Split Curve</span> command can be used to split curves in one of three different methods, to be selected in the 
<span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+143">Mode</span> drop-down list.</p>


<p style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:6px;">First select the curves to be split (the <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+53">Curves</span> item in the selection list will turn to green) and then end selection by right-clicking and selecting 
<span class="UI_COMMAND" id="tdesign.msg+_INTEL_LABEL_+159">Continue</span> in the context menu.</p>


<p style="margin-top:0;">In the <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+143">Mode</span> drop-down list, select the splitting method:</p>


<ul class="noleft" style="margin-bottom:6px;">
<li><span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+66">Points</span>&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;to split one or more selected curves at the points you specify by clicking or using the 
<a href="mk:@MSITStore:selsna.chm::/language/snap/OVfile/T_OV_to_15.htm">Snap</a> tools.</li>


<li><span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+42">Boundaries</span>&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;to split one or more selected curves at their intersections with other curves 
<span id="TWOD">or surfaces (planes, ruled surfaces or NURBS)</span> selected as boundaries. Please note that using the <a href="../HWfile/T_HW_UseExtension.htm">
<span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+199">Extend curves</span></a> option (under 
<span class="UI_COMMAND" id="tdesign.msg+_TDCOMMAND_LABEL_+5">More Options</span>) you can decide whether to split the curves also at its <i>virtual</i> intersections or only at is <i>actual</i> intersections with the boundaries.</li>


<li><span class="UI_COMMAND" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_SPEECH_+145">Arc Joints</span>&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;to split a selected curve at its arc joints (about arc joints in a NURBS curve, see "<a href="../OVfile/T_OV_curves.htm">An Overview On Curves</a>").</li>

</ul>

<p style="margin-bottom:0;" id="HIDEP">The <a href="../OVfile/T_OV_curves.htm#Assoc"><span class="UI_OPTION" id="CurveUI.msg+_CURVE_UI_LABEL_+319">Associative Mode</span></a> check box enables you to create curves which retain a link to the surfaces/curves they derive from.</p>


<table id="F2DNOTVISIBLE">
<tr valign="top">
<td><img src="../../../images/general/bullet_black.gif" align="bottom"></td>
<td>When the check box is selected, the resulting curves will be associative. The new curve will retain a link to the entities it derives from. A specific node displaying both the original entities and the resulting associative curve will be added to the <span class="UI_OPTION" id="tdesign.msg+_EK_ALL_+1685">Model Structure</span>.</td>

</tr>

<tr valign="top">
<td><img src="../../../images/general/bullet_black.gif" align="bottom"></td>
<td>When the check box is cleared, the resulting curves will not be associative.</td>
</tr>
</table>

